flowRoot.flowPara: Transmits everything on all member interfaces
Groups the members at the physical layer to form a single link layer interface
Requires a switch that is 802.3ad compliant
Transmits everything on all member interfaces
Transmit packets in sequential order from the first available member through the last.
This ensures that the same interface is selected for each destination MAC address used.
When the primary member fails, a backup member replaces it as the only active interface.
The outgoing traffic is distributed according to the current load on each member.
Cannot be used behind a bridge with virtual machines
Includes transmit and receive load balancing for IPv4 traffic
Cannot be used behind a bridge with virtual machines
